Package InfrastructureManager.Modules.REST.RawData

Class RESTModuleConfigData

java.lang.Object
InfrastructureManager.ModuleManagement.RawData.ModuleConfigData
InfrastructureManager.Modules.REST.RawData.RESTModuleConfigData
public class RESTModuleConfigData
extends ModuleConfigData
Raw data representing a RESTModule.

To create a REST module the following data is needed: - Name of the module - Port where the REST server will be deployed - Base URL for all requests - List of POSTInputConfigData representing the different POST inputs declared. - List of GETOutputConfigData representing the different GET outputs declared.

Type is automatically selected as ModuleFactory.ModuleType.REST

      public RESTModuleConfigData​(java.lang.String name, int port, java.lang.String baseURL, java.util.List<POSTInputConfigData> inputs, java.util.List<GETOutputConfigData> outputs)
      Creates a new raw REST module. Uses the JsonProperty annotation for extracting information from the "name", "port", "baseURL", "POST" and "GET" fields while deserializing.
      Parameters:
      name - Name of the module
      port - Port where the REST server will be deployed
      baseURL - Base URL for all requests
      inputs - List of raw POST input data representing the different POST inputs declared.
      outputs - List of raw GET output data representing the different GET outputs declared.
